p: Pentadecane was used as an internal standard, and α-pinene, verbenone, terpinolene and α-terpineol were used as external standards. Sixty eight chemical components of SEO were putatively identified by GC-MS analysis, accounting for 92.07% of the total content of essential oil, as shown in Table 1, Figure A1 and Table A1. The major chemical component was α-pinene (26.00%). The other main components were verbenone (7.40%), calarene (5.27%), kaur-16-ene (3.51%) and terpinolene (1.69%). Among the 68 chemical compounds, most of them were monoterpenoids (54.65%), mainly including α-pinene, α-terpineol, verbenone and terpinolene. Sesquiterpenoids content was 22.73%; content of others was 14.69%.
